#
# This document maintains the history of all changes made to the project.
#
# Guidelines for making changes:
# --------------------------------
# - Each change must be added under the correct version number.
# - For each change, categorize it as [Added], [Fixed], [Changed], or [Removed].
# - Add a brief description of the change.
# - Mention the specific area of the code affected, such as the file name or function.
#
# Use the following placeholders and guidelines to log the changes:
# 
# **[Added]**  - Features or functionality added to the project.
# **[Fixed]**  - Bug fixes, errors resolved, or improved functionality.
# **[Changed]** - Modifications to existing code or logic.
# **[Removed]** - Code that was removed or deprecated.
#
# Format each entry as follows:
# - Version:  [Version Number]
# - Date:     [Date of Change]
# - Author:   [Your Name]
# - Change Type: [Added | Fixed | Changed | Removed]
# - Description: [Brief Description of What Was Changed]
#
# ==============================================================================
#
# Example:
# ------------
# Version: 1.0.1
# Date: 2025-12-01
# Author: Anubhav
#
# **[Added]**
# - Added new state handling for "Landing" phase in flight states.
# - Created a function `FlightState_HandleLanding()` in `flight_states.cpp`.
#
# **[Fixed]**
# - Fixed bug in altitude sensor reading that caused incorrect launch state transitions.
#
# ==============================================================================
#
